##A 2n insider interview | Teacher Fei: This is my business, too. What can I do?

Micro Signal Anti

Features A2n, Anti-2019-ncov. A group of folk volunteers whose main work is to popularize science and dispel rumors.

On January 20,2020, the epidemic in Wuhan quickly escalated. A batch of young people act spontaneously, online or offline to fight the epidemic to contribute their own strength, Anti-2019-ncov (abbreviation A2N epidemic situation volunteer group) is one of them.

A2N has opened up a group, Materials Group, Translation Group, popular science and other 11 groups. So far, many volunteers from all over the country have joined A2n.
Although the Sparrow is small, complete, in order to let the A2n in this era of low-light stay a little longer, A2N depth project group for everyone to bring A2n internal interview series.

This issue interviews the object: The local group-refutes the rumor group-in-depth project each group-fan Wenjing

On January 20,2020, the epidemic in Wuhan quickly escalated. A batch of young people act spontaneously, online or offline to fight the epidemic to contribute their own strength, Anti-2019-ncov (abbreviation A2N epidemic situation volunteer group) is one of them.

A2N has opened up a group, Materials Group, Translation Group, popular science and other 11 groups. So far, many volunteers from all over the country have joined A2n.

Although the Sparrow is small, complete, in order to let the A2n in this era of low-light stay a little longer, A2N depth project group for everyone to bring A2n internal interview series.

This issue interviews the object: The local group-refutes the rumor group-in-depth project each group-fan Wenjing

My biggest feeling in A2n is from having fun.
Before joining A2n, I thought that all I could do for a patient to ask for help was to help him or herself, or to empathize with him or her, just about him or her. But what I see is that when joy gets this information, she quickly contacts people, finds local people and volunteers, and helps them connect supplies and give them supplies, for example, send some oximeter, thermometer, mask and other items... from that moment, I have a deeper understanding of the voluntary action I participated in. So now I look at what's happening in the epidemic and I think, this is something about me, too.
Although I would say, why is this so hard? It's hard to watch, but after that, I'll start asking more questions:
"What can I do? "
I've come to believe that a lot of things can really be done if you want to.

A2N.
You know, the whole rumor thing

You know, the whole rumor thing

At first, I was in the fun of the crush group with fun to do refuting rumors.
The rumour mill is A2n's "home base" , where its job is to help people instantly identify information and resist panic.
At that time, refuting rumors was mainly for fun, because refuting rumors for me at that time, is a thing to learn: first joined the group of A2n, hoping to get some reliable information from this group, to help me identify which information is rumors. After this period of study, I have a lot of thinking about refuting rumors. Before I share my experience with you, here are two ways A2n can dispel rumors:

Smash crew refutes rumor. Vs refutes rumor
The way to dispel rumors is to verify the information as soon as a group member posts it, and then verify or falsify the information.

The way of refuting rumors is very similar to the way of "being earnest" , they have a very perfect flow: one person is responsible for the verification of a rumor, the Ta may divide the rumor into several main points, and then distribute them to verify each point one by one; After the fact-finding, they also seek out experts, such as medical experts, to help them examine whether there is a problem; generally, after the series of fact-finding is completed, the results of the fact-finding will be released to the public.

From my point of view, there are two main differences between the two approaches:
1. Time pressure
In the Smash Group, the person in charge of refuting the rumor needs to draw a preliminary conclusion about the content immediately; but in the Smash Group, there is no need to finish refuting the rumor immediately.
2. Whether it is permissible to draw a conclusion first and correct it afterwards
The work of refuting rumors is all within the group, in order to alleviate panic and prevent rumors from spreading. So whether what we say is true or not, we can continue to state it after the fact. Due to the high requirement of timeliness and the limitation of available information, the system has a certain error-tolerance rate. So what we're going to do is make a preliminary judgment based on the information at the time, and try to make that judgment and advice as helpful as possible.
However, the group is on behalf of the A2N platform to release information, so must be very rigorous to verify, if the release of information error, it will inevitably have a negative impact on A2n.
Therefore, the work of refuting rumors group, in fact, is more inclined to be a process based on official information to verify, based on expert information to refute rumors. As the "unofficial channels" of information is doubtful, can not be used as evidence, so there are some rumors can not be verified, the timeliness is not strong.
So, no matter which way of refuting rumors, there is a certain compromise: In the crushing group, it may be the compromise between the timeliness and the expert verification process, or the authority of "I must be absolutely right" before the timeliness; Here at the rumor-dispelling group, there is a compromise on the richness and higher timeliness of the published content.
We all need to compromise, but there is no guarantee that we can all get what we want, and that creates problems. After discovering this, and in order to get to know each other's work, I initiated a conversation that brought together the heads of the shredder group, the rumour mill group, and the translation team for Cross group talks. (the A2N translation team is responsible for the accurate translation of information about the epidemic, breaking down some rumors or one-sided interpretations caused by language barriers.) This conversation, I let the people who want to listen in, in order to let everyone know, what compromises have been made by the three teams in A2n to do the different jobs.
I want you to understand that although we A2N output is some very "official" content, but we actually do a lot of flexible, real-time things internally, there is a lot of "invisible" but perhaps more meaningful work, and I hope you will look at each other, improve understanding, and continue to support each other.
So I outlined, timed, and tried to solve the problem in 10 minutes, but it turned out that just clarifying each other's point of view was a three hour discussion online, as if it wasn't worth it

How do you define "rumor" ?
How can government transparency be promoted to reduce gossip?
How to synthesize different information sources to judge?
What is the difference between factual judgment and professional judgment? WHO's the audience? How are we going to do it?
How do we get the media to help spread our disinformation?

How clear refuels the rumor group and the pulverization unit different localization, and strives for the release more pulverizer content?
Future A2N refutes the rumor content and refutes the rumor dissemination plan?

The purpose of this conversation is not to produce concrete results or outputs, but it is still valuable, not only to let people know what others are doing, but also to let people think more about refuting rumors.

For example, the local community refutes the rumor

For example, the local community refutes the rumor

Later A2n had to do the idea of local group, local group of a lot of work basically belong to my side. There are two people in charge of the local group, the other one besides me is called fage. Our work is divided like this: He is mainly responsible for advancing the content of the group that we have already matured, i'm more responsible for giving advice and help to groups that aren't yet fully operational, but whose owners want our help.
The main tasks of the local clusters are:
Dispel rumors, share information, support each other.
These three things are all things that I think are more important.
The work of refuting rumors of local groups is unique, and its uniqueness lies in its strong locality. For example, prior to the Shanghai appointment mask information, each mask 46 cents, a person can buy 10,4.60 a pack, and made a very long list, the list listed 1,000 shops can be purchased, this kind of information is of interest only to people living in Shanghai and is of little use to people elsewhere.
At that time, we thought this news was very unreliable. Although the content of local groups has local characteristics, the process of refuting rumors is actually the same. To verify this information, we called each of the 1,000 stores on our list to check with the owner. We also looked at the source of the information and found that the original source was a personal number on a Weibo Account. And based on that information, we're going to determine whether it's true or not, we're going to come to a conclusion, and we're going to tell our friends in the group, that this information might be true (because the store owner confirmed it) , but because there's a line for masks, and you can only buy ten at a time, so I suggest you go out and buy them carefully. Although we were able to establish the veracity of this information, the work of refuting rumors should also be done if the information is not verified.

The example of the mask illustrates the special nature of the place. But there are also problems that stem from, but transcend, the localism. So whether it is the process of refuting rumors or the conclusion, in fact, it can give other local groups very timely and valuable reference.
For something as practical as fighting a rumor, I hope you all had better learn it. But when I heard some local group owners said they did not know how to dispel rumors, I was surprised, because in A2N refuting rumors has been a long time work, I thought everyone has mastered this ability.
I understand the reason. Although we have been helping people answer some of the rumor questions, and the process of answering them is presented in the group, people seem to be less concerned about how the rumor is confirmed or disproved, people are more concerned about whether the content itself is true or false. People are going to look at it, they're going to use it, they're not going to look at it in our group, and that's because they think it's OK to give results.
But we still want to tell you why this is true, why is it false? What are you going to do about it in the future? So that night I communicated with a lot of group owners, fortunately, you still want to understand how to do refuting rumors, I think as long as you want to understand, it is necessary to carry out a course of refuting rumors.
Then I had fun with the other two speakers, who wanted to make the rumor-fighting work more professional, so we produced an article on the methodology of refuting rumors (posted on both our public accounts and Weibo, you can check it out) .
After presenting this methodology to you, there are people in the main group of the local group who want to prove the truth of a rumor, and I encourage them to use this rumor as a case study and practice the methodology they learned the other day.
After that, I will answer this question step by step in the group: First, you need to confirm whether this person's identity and position is consistent with what he said, and secondly, whether this interview that he said actually happened, then we need to see if the transcript of his chat is consistent with the original, and then we need to understand the transcript one by one, and if what it says is consistent with what we understand, and then we'll see if it makes any medical sense... and that's it. One step at a time.

But because this example is really difficult and has some professional barriers, Hu, who worked with me on the rumor documents, suggested that we divide rumors into two categories:
One is the fact that the rumor is either true or false, so we must immediately know from the public information, or some very simple verification, whether it happened or not? Of all the messages, this is mostly the kind that needs to be refuted.
Others, which are similar to those in the above cases, may have some logical problems or scientific errors, but due to the limitations of our own knowledge, we can not immediately identify them, so when refuting rumors, we want to learn knowledge while screening, undoubtedly this process is more difficult.

Indeed, the matter of refuting rumors is difficult, and people tend to shy away from difficulties. But I think it means something.

A2N.
For example, small jobs in local communities

For example, small jobs in local communities

At present, local groups generally do not have too many rumors, not to dispel rumors, our ideas and attitude to the local group is that if the group is not active does not matter, it does not have to be active in order to have value. If the situation on the ground isn't serious and people aren't panicking, then it's Ok for the group to just share information with people. Even if the group were to cease to operate for a day, there would be no problem. But if this group is active, and there are a lot of rumors circulating within the group, and it is easy to cause panic, then we will certainly step in and try to find someone to run the rumor-dispelling work.

A2N local group will set up the main group, generally speaking, the main group by everyone self-recommendation, I and fage will choose from among them. The criteria are: to speak out in the group, and his speech can make people feel his ability and willingness to lead the work. For example: they want to get information flowing, they are willing to share information in groups, they are willing to explore the authenticity of information. This is the type of person we would rather choose as the leader of the group. In addition, I hope that this group can take the initiative to think, initiative to figure out how to do more for everyone.
Different local groups will do different things according to their own conditions. Some of the group owners are doing things like organizing local documents, including important information about what is happening locally, information about local designated hospitals, and public news, may also collate the infected person's situation, the infected person's movement path and so on, has done the very detailed degree. The Shandong cluster of A2n, for example, was started by a group of programmers who created a local outbreak site, which is now a project at the level of the entire A2n volunteer group. Other groups may be working with local volunteer teams to do something similar to help with the local docking.

In general, each group owner can do different things if they have different resources and want to do different things. We don't limit what each local group needs to do, and we don't say what you should do. But we will keep an eye on their needs and do everything we can to help them from the A2n community.
The A2N local group that I understand has strong decentralized properties. The initial centralization was due to the sponsor's proposal that anyone who wanted to do an A2n branch could do it using the A2n main document. Our documents are not copyrighted and can be used whenever you want, whether in a place or industry, as long as you have something you want to do or are good at. We don't set any limits, and we don't take the initiative to build stronger links when we don't have to.
In the management of local groups, we have no restrictions and do not require everyone to do things, this is a more suitable way for local groups. This may be called "decentralization" . It is not an insistence, it is not a fixed idea, it is such a kind of existence.
The rest of the group, basically, the person in charge decides what to do and then hands out tasks to the group; or they have a meeting to discuss what to do after the decision has been made. But the local group is basically a "do it yourself first, then ask me questions" model. I rarely give you specific requirements, because the local group does not have to do things. But maybe because there are no such rules, people are looking for what they need to do, and they actually do it.
Sometimes, however, coordinating groups of resources to get things done requires some centralization, such as when A2n wants to do something from the top down. Two days ago in Shanghai Group, there is a small partner has a batch of supplies in Shanghai, hope to find the Shanghai small partner transport, we will send a message in the group. And when we needed volunteers for the outbreak map, we needed someone from Heilongjiang to help us input the route information of the infected, so we went to the Heilongjiang Group and sent that information.
In fact, you will find that this and "decentralization" can be parallel, there is no contradiction. The key is to find the best way to do it. There's a lot of that going around, but it's easy to deal with, you just have to go to the group and ask. The reason that local groups can give strong support may also be that local groups themselves grow better in the practice of decentralization.

I feel the power of "we. "

I feel the power of "we. "

In addition to dispelling rumors and working with local groups, I also initiated a private volunteer reflection project in the deep project group. Because I wanted to have a different conversation with the media as a fellow volunteer. Because I volunteered in the outbreak, I have a very emotional understanding of the outbreak, so I know roughly how the other volunteers work, and I know when there's going to be an emotional wave, when are people gonNA think rationally.
We want to talk to people like A2n, who have been mobilized because of the epidemic, not a well-established social organization. I would think that in the process, there is a personal space for thinking about the development of non-governmental organization, and I think it is valuable.
And I want to find more teams that are likely to be small, unfocused, but doing things all the time. Because there is a certain consistency in what people say to the outside world that has been reported many times, so I want to talk to people who aren't reported as much, and I want to hear their voices, understand what they do and how they do it.
I want to introduce these teams to the public, so that you can see what they're doing, and record your thoughts. I know some groups that actually think a lot, but no one writes it down, and I want to help them write it down, because it's valuable. I think it's valuable to keep more current records, whether they're infected, experienced, or volunteer.
I also want to document the changes in their work. During the course of the epidemic change, the A2N material group made a lot of changes. At the beginning, we could dock medical materials, such as masks, protective clothing, and so on. As the government began to take over the unified distribution of medical materials, we went to the hospital to send some supplies and food, and then the hospital in Wuhan was no longer so short of supplies, and we went to focus on the needs of other remote areas of Hubei. Well, it's not just the supply team, but almost all of our teams have had some sort of adjustment. So I started to wonder, what did the other volunteer teams think, what adjustments did they make?
This gradual understanding of the process, A2N itself is also of great significance, we will go to reflect on what we do now? What can A2n do on its own? Others do a good place, A2n can also learn from it? Or say others feel that there is no way to do things, A2n can help to complete together? These are also very valuable.
(I and two other partners, wrote some very valuable interviews, not here, Amway everyone to see the micro-blog A2n. Would like to join the project partners, please contact me.)

And then there are the other touches that came out of the interview with my subject:
One of my interviewees, the head of the selection panel, told me that it was as if
Seeing that I've put together so much of what I've been talking to them for two hours, completely gets them to say what they want to say, very accurately, with almost no misunderstandings. I also saw a note on the document said, "shouldn't this place be written more clearly, don't be afraid to delete the article, that place has a good feeling, you can write in another direction... ". And so it is, heart and get.
Ta suddenly felt, can do volunteer, or say, can write such articles, can pay attention to such things, seems to be the same kind of people. You guys, it's really similar.
We're all so sure of the meaning and value of what we do -- I feel like it makes sense, I want to keep more, I want to do more... ... On this basis, how we can make our contribution outside the official and mainstream channels, how we can see the "less visible" people who need help, how to do more with their own power... for many of the "how, " the view, will be very similar.
This time, as a volunteer, I had a strong feeling. At first, I felt that I had met many new people. However, as I got to know each other gradually, it turned out that most people would get to know each other in real life, even if they didn't know each other through A2n, i met a lot of women's rights people, or a lot of other practitioners. It seems to me that the people who follow these kinds of public events are the same people. I had a feeling that if I didn't know him here, I would know him somewhere else.
I felt the power of "we, " which transformed me:
This time I launched two deep projects at A2n, both of which I felt valuable and wanted to do, and I did. But I've never done anything like this before, and most of the time it's like, I think it's funny, I want to do it, and then I do it and I'm like, oh, it's so hard, I can't do it, I can't do it, I can't do what I want to do, i don't feel very happy.
Then this time I will find that I can also find some like-minded people to work together, we are good at different things, but can really make more valuable things from their strengths.
Oh! I am happy. Very happy.

In addition to dispelling rumors and working with local groups, I also initiated a private volunteer reflection project in the deep project group. Because I wanted to have a different conversation with the media as a fellow volunteer. Because I volunteered in the outbreak, I have a very emotional understanding of the outbreak, so I know roughly how the other volunteers work, and I know when there's going to be an emotional wave, when are people gonNA think rationally.

We want to talk to people like A2n, who have been mobilized because of the epidemic, not a well-established social organization. I would think that in the process, there is a personal space for thinking about the development of non-governmental organization, and I think it is valuable.

And I want to find more teams that are likely to be small, unfocused, but doing things all the time.
